<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 2:41PM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Richland, Morrow,
southeastern Crawford and northwestern Knox Counties through 330 PM
EDT...
At 241 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Galion to near Ashley to Powell. Movement
was northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Mansfield, Mount Gilead, Galion, Shelby, Ontario, Lexington,
Crestline, Fredericktown, Cardington, Bellville, Ashley,
Chesterville, Sparta, Waterford, Butler, Lucas, Edison, Marengo,
Fulton and North Liberty.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
